          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1535.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>focaccia breads</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 6-7 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-2.new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-2.new-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-2.new-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-2.new-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-2.new-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pat the <strong>rump steaks</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\n<p>Once the pan is very hot, add the <strong>steaks</strong> and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p><strong>For medium-rare</strong>, cook for 2-3 min on each side</p>\n<p><strong>For medium</strong>, cook for 3-4 min on each side</p>\n<p><strong>For rare</strong>, cook for 2 min max on each side</p>\n<p>Once the steaks are cooked, transfer them to a plate to rest and reserve the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p>\n<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>garlic</strong> roughly  </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1746.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
